My Dear girlie: -Feb. 8th 1927
Your photo sits on my <unclear/> by my side and Has hardly had time to get warm since the Post man brot it-I look and look and then some more - you surely have not changed except your hair and it is so pretty.- Of course they are satisfied I have known it thru Dr Comm and Dr House- Mona said this morning where we got the photo-"Oh darn it why doesn't some good man grab her"-you must be very busy and I'm glad you are satisfied-It is so sweet of you to want to know about 
