sure she will do something with the violin yet Alice-will to my notions is the finest of them all-she was started to school after they came to Kirkwood-but the little thing got so homesick and she is not in school now-she is not standing still how ever is spelling every thing and writing to, and the questions she asks would keep a wise man buy. So we think she will <unclear/> little by being out this year. - She was five in Aug. When she saw your photo she said I think that is a nice face.-We are hoping she will sing, she is the only one of the children who ever sang around their play. - I expect to go home in a couple weeks. - am going to St. Louis to visit some people I met in Buffalo tomorrow. We go to a reception given for John by the Literary association of Kirkwood tonight will tell you all about it later lovingly alice m. neihardt. 
am in a big hurry

